Description: Xcode 26.5 ships libc++ 20 which cleaned up transitive includes;
libs/mysql/gtid/tag_plain.h uses std::is_trivial_v / std::is_standard_layout_v
(lines 83-84) but never includes <type_traits>, relying on it being pulled in
through <string>/<memory>. Under the 26.5 SDK this breaks:
  error: no template named 'is_trivial_v' in namespace 'std'
The fix is the standard one-line include. Upstream MySQL Bug #120807 (trunk
still unfixed as of 9.7.0 release).

--- a/libs/mysql/gtid/tag_plain.h
+++ b/libs/mysql/gtid/tag_plain.h
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 #include <array>
 #include <cstring>
 #include <memory>
 #include <string>
+#include <type_traits>
 
 #include "mysql/gtid/gtid_constants.h"  // tag_max_length
